14:25.198 --> 14:27.181
♪<i> The mayor, it's said</i> ♪

14:27.200 --> 14:29.092
♪<i> Had rocks in his head</i> ♪

14:29.110 --> 14:32.945
♪<i> And he went by the name</i>
<i> of Van Houten...</i> ♪

14:33.022 --> 14:34.038
My history!

14:34.190 --> 14:35.540
ALL:
My choice!

14:35.691 --> 14:37.876
Our gazebo was "noice!"

14:38.027 --> 14:39.860
Please, please, everyone.

14:39.880 --> 14:41.621
It's the holidays.

14:41.715 --> 14:44.215
Can't we just find common ground
and compromise?

14:44.367 --> 14:47.385
I mean, the one thing
both sides can agree on

14:47.536 --> 14:50.613
is that we all
care about our kids,

14:50.615 --> 14:52.039
equally.

14:52.133 --> 14:54.467
Marge, you are so right,

14:54.619 --> 14:56.636
but there's only one side
that I'm afraid

14:56.788 --> 14:59.546
will burn this whole
godforsaken town to the ground.

14:59.566 --> 15:00.714
Burn it!

15:00.734 --> 15:03.309
Stop teaching
the damn gazebo collapse.

15:03.461 --> 15:07.146
Mr. Mayor, my whole career,
I have fought tirelessly to...

15:07.298 --> 15:09.073
Damn it, Gary,
it's just one thing.

15:09.300 --> 15:11.300
Fine.
Who gives a crap?

15:11.319 --> 15:14.746
Wow.
I actually won something.

15:14.897 --> 15:16.822
Let's get ready

15:16.975 --> 15:19.492
to meddle!

15:19.586 --> 15:21.978
(cheering)

15:21.996 --> 15:25.331
Oh. I'm getting
a sick feeling in my stomach.

15:25.483 --> 15:28.426
Oh, don't worry so much, honey.

15:28.503 --> 15:31.170
People just want
to feel proud of our town.

15:31.264 --> 15:34.006
And remember,
I'm still on the school board,

15:34.100 --> 15:35.341
so I can be a guardrail

15:35.435 --> 15:38.177
to keep Kirk's
worst impulses in check.

15:38.329 --> 15:41.497
I mean, how bad can it be?

15:41.516 --> 15:43.733
(bombastic music playing
over speakers)

15:50.099 --> 15:52.099
Wow, I can't believe
all this happened

15:52.118 --> 15:54.160
in only three weeks.

16:01.686 --> 16:04.128
<i> NARRATOR:</i>
<i> So the people surrendered</i>
<i> to Van Houten's wishes,</i>

16:04.280 --> 16:06.613
<i>and his face was on everything,</i>

16:06.633 --> 16:08.040
<i> even knishes.</i>

16:08.209 --> 16:10.617
<i>But for Springfield, the outcome</i>

16:10.695 --> 16:12.804
<i> was rather pernicious.</i>

16:12.955 --> 16:15.789
<i> ANNOUNCER: It's the</i> Channel 6
News<i> with Kent Brockman.</i>

16:15.809 --> 16:18.384
♪ ♪

16:18.461 --> 16:20.561
(cheering)

16:22.207 --> 16:25.224
<i> Brought to you by</i>
<i> Homer's House of Copper-ganda,</i>

16:25.376 --> 16:28.969
<i> your one-stop shop</i>
<i> for form-fitting Kirk-wear.</i>

16:28.989 --> 16:30.730
Good evening, and all hail Kirk.

16:30.882 --> 16:32.231
Our top story:

16:32.325 --> 16:34.826
<i> The Springfield bookmobile</i>
<i> visits a local landmark,</i>

16:34.902 --> 16:37.478
<i> which is getting a new name.</i>

16:37.497 --> 16:38.997
I re-christen thee

16:39.224 --> 16:40.647
The Eternal Flame

16:40.742 --> 16:43.226
of Redaction and Beauty.

16:43.244 --> 16:45.745
You said you'd only burn
half the books.

16:45.839 --> 16:47.321
Half? No way.

16:47.340 --> 16:49.232
This is all part of my plan

16:49.325 --> 16:53.052
to turn eyesores
into pride-sores.

16:57.500 --> 16:58.599
(cheering)

17:04.524 --> 17:06.357
I didn't sleep a wink.

17:06.584 --> 17:10.153
I can fix that.
I'll adjust your copper number.

17:12.973 --> 17:15.349
Aah!
(exclaiming)

17:15.368 --> 17:18.018
Homer, things are terrible
in this town.

17:18.112 --> 17:20.112
Kirk got a little bit
of power to control

17:20.206 --> 17:22.540
what the kids learn
and he went cuckoo with it,

17:22.691 --> 17:24.267
and we helped him.

17:24.360 --> 17:25.951
I just really thought I could be

17:26.104 --> 17:28.195
the grown-up in the room.

17:28.214 --> 17:30.364
Yeah, 'cause that always works.

17:30.383 --> 17:33.217
I've got to do something
to save Springfield

17:33.294 --> 17:35.219
and I need you to help me.

17:35.371 --> 17:38.114
Great idea.
What's in it for me?

17:38.207 --> 17:40.707
Homer, what does it profit a man

17:40.802 --> 17:42.134
if he gains the world

17:42.287 --> 17:44.470
but loses his soul?

17:44.622 --> 17:46.547
Uh, he gains the world.

17:46.566 --> 17:48.958
(gasps)
I got to put that on a shirt.

17:48.976 --> 17:50.401
D'oh...

17:54.723 --> 17:56.465
Hey there, great leader.

17:56.484 --> 17:59.635
You're looking especially
non-repulsive today.

17:59.637 --> 18:02.988
With great power comes great
"you have to like me."

18:03.141 --> 18:04.990
-(chuckles) Mwah.
-(moans)

18:05.159 --> 18:06.584
(both moaning)

18:06.735 --> 18:08.811
Um, uh, e-excuse me.

18:08.830 --> 18:11.589
Marge, my guardrail.
Have a seat.

18:13.760 --> 18:15.318
So, what's the good word?

18:15.320 --> 18:17.929
And I only want good words.

18:18.080 --> 18:20.747
Ugh. I know you don't
want to hear it, Kirk,

18:20.916 --> 18:23.326
but our schools are a disaster.

18:23.344 --> 18:24.936
Reading levels have plummeted

18:25.087 --> 18:27.921
because there are no books left
for kids to read.

18:28.015 --> 18:30.924
Sure, but those books
were bummers.

18:30.944 --> 18:32.110
They're not bummers,

18:32.261 --> 18:34.094
they're the sum
of human knowledge.

18:34.114 --> 18:37.173
You can't base
an entire society on ignorance

18:37.191 --> 18:39.342
and forgetting the past.

18:39.360 --> 18:40.952
Hmm.

18:41.103 --> 18:43.679
Marge, thank you
for telling me all this.

18:43.698 --> 18:45.123
Top-notch guardrailing.

18:45.274 --> 18:49.460
I know now this moment
calls for serious action.

18:50.797 --> 18:52.130
Damn it.

18:52.357 --> 18:54.357
(rock band playing)

18:54.375 --> 18:56.283
So how about this gazebo?

18:56.361 --> 18:59.137
It's twice as big
as the original...

18:59.288 --> 19:01.639
which never existed.

19:01.866 --> 19:04.200
(cheering)

19:04.293 --> 19:07.036
I declare we have won the war

19:07.054 --> 19:08.813
against history.

19:08.964 --> 19:10.815
(cheering)

19:10.966 --> 19:12.725
It's time to rock out

19:12.877 --> 19:14.735
with your Kirk out.

19:15.897 --> 19:19.198
The past never happened!

19:20.326 --> 19:22.368
(whimpering)

19:24.330 --> 19:25.580
(grunting)

19:28.017 --> 19:29.149
What is happening?

19:29.169 --> 19:31.169
Uh, the electricity
running through

19:31.396 --> 19:33.654
everyone's copper T-shirts
has created

19:33.748 --> 19:35.322
a massive electrical field

19:35.416 --> 19:38.083
and a full-fledged
magnetic disturbance.

19:38.236 --> 19:39.735
Dumb it down for us.

19:39.754 --> 19:41.070
Well, I just did.

19:41.088 --> 19:42.588
(stammers)

19:42.682 --> 19:43.997
(groaning)

19:44.017 --> 19:46.742
Soup crackers!

19:46.761 --> 19:48.227
(crying)

19:57.605 --> 19:59.197
(groans)

20:00.942 --> 20:02.591
Attention, everyone.

20:02.593 --> 20:05.369
We learned something
very important today.

20:05.596 --> 20:07.613
You can try to ignore history,

20:07.765 --> 20:09.782
but not science.

20:09.934 --> 20:11.934
No matter how much we deny it,

20:12.027 --> 20:13.769
science is real,

20:13.862 --> 20:16.455
and we must not anger her.

20:16.532 --> 20:18.424
(all assenting)

